<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-10-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="678" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d678">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Swenson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 220</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-10-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your No. 128, of the 10th ultimo, transmitting copy of a new
                            draft of treaty for the proposed cession of the Danish West Indies to
                            the United States, embodying the accepted suggestions made in the note
                            from the Danish Minister for Foreign Affairs, of June 29, last, a copy
                            of which was communicated to the Department in my No. 212, dated
                            Norseland, Minnesota, August 8, 1901.</p>
                        <p>A copy of the amended project has been handed to the Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Laurits S. Swenson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>